.TH "__mmc_claim_host" 9 "__mmc_claim_host" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__mmc_claim_host \- exclusively claim a host
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __mmc_claim_host
.BI "(struct mmc_host *host "  ","
.BI "struct mmc_ctx *ctx "  ","
.BI "atomic_t *abort "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "host" 12
mmc host to claim
.IP "ctx" 12
context that claims the host or NULL in which case the default
context will be used
.IP "abort" 12
whether or not the operation should be aborted

Claim a host for a set of operations.  If \fIabort\fP is non null and
dereference a non-zero value then this will return prematurely with
that non-zero value without acquiring the lock.  Returns zero
with the lock held otherwise.
